- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with 3D human pose estimation, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions applications in collaborative and service robotics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses training data augmentation as a method to improve occlusion-robustness, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing methods to improve the performance of AI systems in realistic human-robot shared environments. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions synthetic occlusions, which may involve graphics techniques.
